Comments: Site varies from medium to good.  Tree performance seems uniform.
Forest.Health: Some forking in stand (<5%), minor sweep (speed wobbles) in 30% of stems.
Competition: Espacement normal (~ 1000 stems/ha) and no overstory competition.

Comments: Good site but steep w/ heavy snow load, burned.
Forest.Health: Too much snow and frost damage too accept Fdi at this elevation.
Competition: Likely early competition from  shrubs delaying early height growth.

Comments: Good site, not a significant factor
Forest.Health: Some sweep, occasional forking (? environmental factors)
Competition: No significant competition from density or overtopping deciduous

Comments: Moderate site, south facing
Forest.Health: Fewer forks, crooks and sweep than in other Fdi stands. Not a significant factor at plot. In general approximately 15% incidence
Competition: Dead overstory Pl generally sparse and weren't likely a significant factor. No other competition concerns

Comments: Poor site, rocky ridge top
Forest.Health: Many forks at young age (stunted trees)
Competition: Tree competition not an issue

Comments: Medium site, warm and well drained.  Good for Fd.
Forest.Health: Occasional forking.  Not common.
Competition: Not a significant adverse factor for dom and co-dom trees.  Some of the suppressed trees could be Fd seed-in

Comments: Good site.  Heavy thimbleberry in openings my have been a contributing factor in survival.
Forest.Health: No major FHFs evident.
Competition: Not a significant factor.

Comments: Good to medium site.  No concerns.  No chance of cold air ponding.  Doesn't appear to have been broadcast burned.
Forest.Health: Nothing significant.  Difficult to see tops but little forking apparent.
Competition: Spacing tight (~1800/ha).  Canopy closed and very little brush in understory.

Comments: Not a significant factor.
Forest.Health: Frost caused mortality and top damage common.  Lot of bear claw marks on Fd but not Pl.
Competition: Overtopping Pl caused Fd suppression in some areas of the stand.

Comments: Medium site (01 poor). Warm aspect. Areas upslope with stonier dryer soils.
Forest.Health: Lot of top kill and forks (>50%) due to frost.
Competition: Location of individual seedlot unknown.

Comments: Poor site at top of plot, medium midslope, and good on lower slope.  Warm aspect, well drained.  Generally good survival.
Forest.Health: 5% forking - frost?
Competition: Not a significant factor although there are a few trees in dense patches that are moribund.

Comments: Good site. Likely early brush competition.  Good aspect.
Forest.Health: Probably some frost damage causing minor forking.  Most trees quickly re-established a dominant leader.
Competition: Not a significant issue.

Comments: Good site.  Moderate brush.  Seepage. No cold air ponding.  Warm aspect.
Forest.Health: Occasional forking.
Competition: Not a significant factor at the plot.  In other areas ingress may have caused some mortality.

Comments: Good site.  Brush moderately heavy in openings (Rupa, Alvi, herbs).  Good growth.  Fd leaders 30-40 cm.
Forest.Health: Good survival at plot and low incidence of frost damage (although not absent).
Competition: Fd above Alvi and so not a significant factor at this point although brush could have been a factor in early survival.

Comments: Medium site. Moderate brush.  No cold air ponding.  Not a significant factor.
Forest.Health: Evidence of frost damage minimal.  No other significant forest health issues.
Competition: Some Fd with slow initial growth not in main canopy.  Some natural stocking may have had an early height advantage.

Comments: Medium site.  Stony w/some seepage.  Warm aspect.  No cold air ponding.
Forest.Health: Few forest health factors.  Not significant.
Competition: Moderate interspecific competition.  May have played a minor role in slow growth for some trees.

Comments: Generally good site.  Moderate brush.  No cold air ponding.
Forest.Health: Occasional broken stem (snow loading) and forks (frost) although relatively uncommon.
Competition: No overtopping Pl or Hw on this side of the road and only the slowest growing Fd affected.  Not broadcast burned.  Survival seems good although original planting density unknown.

Comments: Medium site.  Not frost prone although the NW aspect is not ideal.  Brush (Alnus) is moderate.
Forest.Health: Some snow press.  Areas where top kill is more prevalent.
Competition: Not a significant adverse factor

Comments: Good site although north and west aspect.
Forest.Health: Very few issues (see Lw8(2))
Competition: Not a significant factor.  Some small Lw, possibly a result of selfing.

Comments: Good site, better than average, some seepage.
Forest.Health: Nothing evident in Lw
Competition: Competition not abnormal (i.e. espacement correct)

Comments: Good site, toe of slope, seepage
Forest.Health: Relatively minor forking and sweep from frost and snow.
Competition: Tree competition minor.  Brush may have been a factor in early survival.

Comments: Med to poor site.  Very stony.  Some seepage.  Possible cold air ponding.  Seedlot probably inappropriate.
Forest.Health: Areas with high incidence (>50%) forks, dead tops, snow press and sweep.  Likely all frost and snow.
Competition: Pockets of higher Pl and Bl stocking with moderate brush.  Not a serious problem though.

Comments: Good site.  Brush moderately heavy.
Forest.Health: High incidence of scars at base plus some bent stems at base from snow press.
Competition: Conifer competition not a significant factor (nor deciduous).

Comments: Site poor to medium.  Dry site on most of plot.
Forest.Health: Frost may have been responsible for poor survival.  Some dead tops on other Lw in area (1-4 years die back)
Competition: Not a factor for trees 1-4.  Tree 6 in particular is surrounded by Pl and completely overtopped.

Comments: Poor site, low brush.  Dry site may have contributed to poor survival.
Forest.Health: Not much evident.  Some snow press and top damage due to frost.
Competition: Survival not great but generally good form on surviving trees.  Relatively few forks.  Occasional snow press on spindly stems (see photo).  Fairly high variability in stem size in Lw
